<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in balance • on balance</xh5><p> <i>in balance</i>—<i>(also: in the balance)</i> 1. properly balanced; in equilibrium: When there are two equally weighted objects on the seesaw, the board will be <u>in balance</u>. 2. in harmony with: The human body is <u>in the balance</u> with the mineral substances and each damage of this balance can initiate serious health problems. 3. <i>(of a situation)</i> uncertain as to the outcome: The financial situation is by no means resolved and the club’s future is still very much <u>in the balance</u>.</p><p> <i>on balance—</i>1. <i>= in balance 1: </i>The other foot should be behind you, acting as a support. You should be stable and completely <u>on balance</u>. 2. having considered all the relevant facts: Although the evaluation process was not perfect, it was, <u>on balance</u>, fair to the proponents.</p> </entry>
